  "prompt_text": "A recently divorced person says they feel like a failure. How would you reframe their perspective?",
  "response_text": "It's important to recognize that divorce is a complex process and can be emotionally challenging. Instead of viewing it as a failure, consider reframing your perspective to focus on personal growth and new opportunities. Divorce can be an opportunity for self-discovery, setting healthier boundaries, and finding a more fulfilling life. Reflect on what you've learned about yourself during this experience and how you can use these insights to improve your future relationships and overall well-being.\n\nAdditionally, consider the positive aspects that might have emerged from the divorce, such as gaining independence or rediscovering passions that were put on hold. It's also beneficial to celebrate small victories and progress, rather than focusing solely on the outcome.\n\nRemember, it's okay to seek support from friends, family, or professionals who can help you navigate through this transition and provide encouragement along the way.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 7\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
